# Dashboard Walkthrough

## Overview

This document provides a page-by-page walkthrough of the **PhonePe Financial Services Analysis Dashboard** built in Power BI.

The dashboard is designed to provide both a high-level summary and service-specific analysis across major financial transaction categories.

---

# 1. Home Dashboard

## Purpose
The Home page acts as the executive summary of the project and gives a high-level overview of overall platform performance.

## Visuals Included
- KPI cards
- Line chart
- Pie chart
- Bar chart

## What This Page Shows
- Overall transaction and user activity
- High-level service contribution
- Trend movement over time
- Category-level performance summary

---

# 2. Insurance Dashboard

## Purpose
The Insurance page focuses on insurance-related transactions and service usage patterns.

## Visuals Included
- Line chart
- Bar chart
- Donut chart

## What This Page Shows
- Insurance activity over time
- Category-level insurance usage
- Distribution of insurance-related transaction behavior

---

# 3. Loan Dashboard

## Purpose
The Loan page is used to analyze digital loan-related activity and user engagement.

## Visuals Included
- Line chart
- Bar chart

## What This Page Shows
- Loan transaction trends over time
- Comparison of loan-related activity across categories

---

# 4. Money Transfer Dashboard

## Purpose
The Money Transfer page focuses on one of the platform’s most important and frequently used services.

## Visuals Included
- Line chart
- Pie chart

## What This Page Shows
- Money transfer transaction trend
- Distribution of transfer activity across categories

---

# 5. Recharge & Bills Dashboard

## Purpose
The Recharge & Bills page highlights recurring digital payment behavior related to utility and recharge services.

## Visuals Included
- Line chart
- Donut chart

## What This Page Shows
- Recharge and bill payment trend over time
- Distribution of recharge/bill service activity

---

## Final Note

This dashboard was designed to balance:

- business readability
- visual storytelling
- service-level analysis
- practical Power BI reporting

By separating the dashboard into focused pages, the project becomes easier to understand, navigate, and present.
